; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures PCU module and reads a target port.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting target port with a suitable instrument.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. PCU     : PA0/PA1/PA2/PA3/PA14/PA15 (Input)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; PCU (PAx)
; 1. Port Group                   : 0 (PCU Port A)
;
; 2. Port                         : [ 0 0 i i ] [ 0 1 i i ] [ 0 2 i i ] [ 0 3 i i ] [ 0 14 i i ] [ 0 15 i i ]
;    Pin Number                   : 0 / 1 / 2 / 3 / 14 / 15
;    Pin Mode                     : i (input)
;    Pin Output Mode              : i (input)
;
; 3. Input                        : [ 0 0 ], [ 0 1 ], [ 0 2 ], [ 0 3 ], [ 0 14 ], [ 0 15 ]
;    Pin Number                   : 0, 1, 2, 3, 14, 15
;
; PCU (PA0)
sendln 'cm pcu'
pause 1
sendln 'port 0 0 i i'
pause 1
sendln 'input 0 0'
pause 1

; PCU (PA1)
sendln 'port 0 1 i i'
pause 1
sendln 'input 0 1'
pause 1

; PCU (PA2)
sendln 'port 0 2 i i'
pause 1
sendln 'input 0 2'
pause 1

; PCU (PA3)
sendln 'port 0 3 i i'
pause 1
sendln 'input 0 3'
pause 1

; PCU (PA14)
sendln 'port 0 14 i i'
pause 1
sendln 'input 0 14'
pause 1

; PCU (PA15)
sendln 'port 0 15 i i'
pause 1
sendln 'input 0 15'
pause 1
